  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Confusional-awakening">
    <rdfs:label>Confusional-awakening</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Episode of non epileptic nature included in NREM parasomnias, characterized by sudden arousal and complex behavior but without full alertness, usually lasting a few minutes and occurring almost in all children at least occasionally. Amnesia of the episode is the rule.</rdfs:comment>
