    <rdfs:label>Benign-sleep-myoclonus</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A distinctive disorder of sleep characterized by a) neonatal onset, b) rhythmic myoclonic jerks only during sleep and c) abrupt and consistent cessation with arousal, d) absence of concomitant electrographic changes suggestive of seizures, and e) good outcome.</rdfs:comment>
