  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#PaleGreen">
    <rdfs:label>PaleGreen</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>CSS-color 0x98FB98.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Green-color"/>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Thumb">
    <rdfs:label>Thumb</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>The thick and short hand digit which is next to the index finger in humans.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Finger"/>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Slow-alpha-variant-rhythm">
    <rdfs:label>Slow-alpha-variant-rhythm</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Characteristic rhythms mostly at 4-5 Hz, recorded most prominently over the posterior regions of the head. Generally alternate, or are intermixed, with alpha rhythm to which they often are harmonically related. Amplitude varies but is frequently close to 50 micro V. Blocked or attenuated by attention, especially visual, and mental effort. Comment: slow alpha variant rhythms should be distinguished from posterior slow waves characteristic of children and adolescents and occasionally seen in young adults.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Physiologic-pattern"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Brain-laterality"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Brain-region"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Sensors"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Appearance-mode"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Discharge-pattern"/>
    <heda:inLibrary>score</heda:inLibrary>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Snow">
    <rdfs:label>Snow</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>CSS-color 0xFFFAFA.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#White-color"/>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedPlaceholder rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Screen-resolution-Placeholder">
    <rdfs:label>#</rdfs:label>
    <hed:hasHedParent>
      <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Screen-resolution">
        <rdfs:label>Screen-resolution</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Resolution of a screen, usually expressed as the of pixels in a dimension for a digital display device.</rdfs:comment>
        <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Data-resolution"/>
      </hed:HedTag>
    </hed:hasHedParent>
    <heda:takesValue rdf:datatype="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean">true</heda:takesValue>
    <heda:valueClass rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/aux#numericClass"/>
  </hed:HedPlaceholder>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Semiology-dyscognitive">
    <rdfs:label>Semiology-dyscognitive</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>The term describes events in which (1) disturbance of cognition is the predominant or most apparent feature, and (2a) two or more of the following components are involved, or (2b) involvement of such components remains undetermined. Otherwise, use the more specific term (e.g., mnemonic experiential seizure  or hallucinatory experiential seizure). Components of cognition: ++ perception: symbolic conception of sensory information ++ attention: appropriate selection of a principal perception or task ++ emotion: appropriate affective significance of a perception ++ memory: ability to store and retrieve percepts or concepts ++ executive function: anticipation, selection, monitoring of consequences, and initiation of motor activity including praxis, speech.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent>
      <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Semiology-non-motor-manifestation">
        <rdfs:label>Semiology-non-motor-manifestation</rdfs:label>
        <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Seizure-semiology-manifestation"/>
        <heda:inLibrary>score</heda:inLibrary>
      </hed:HedTag>
    </hed:hasHedParent>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Episode-event-count"/>
    <heda:inLibrary>score</heda:inLibrary>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <owl:AnnotationProperty rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/attributes/#unitProperty">
    <rdfs:subPropertyOf rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed#schemaProperty"/>
    <rdfs:range rdf:resource="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#boolean"/>
    <rdfs:label>unitProperty</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Indicates that the schema attribute is meant to be applied to units within a unit class.</rdfs:comment>
  </owl:AnnotationProperty>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Paper">
    <rdfs:label>Paper</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A thin sheet material produced by mechanically or chemically processing cellulose fibres derived from wood, rags, grasses or other vegetable sources in water.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Manufactured-material"/>
  </hed:HedTag>
