  </hed:HedUnit>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#EMG-artifact">
    <rdfs:label>EMG-artifact</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>Myogenic potentials are the most common artifacts. Frontalis and temporalis muscles (ex..: clenching of jaw muscles) are common causes. Generally, the potentials generated in the muscles are of shorter duration than those generated in the brain. The frequency components are usually beyond 30-50 Hz, and the bursts are arrhythmic.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Biological-artifact"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Brain-laterality"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Brain-region"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Sensors"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Multifocal-finding"/>
    <heda:suggestedTag rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Artifact-significance-to-recording"/>
    <heda:inLibrary>score</heda:inLibrary>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Elbow">
    <rdfs:label>Elbow</rdfs:label>
    <rdfs:comment>A type of hinge joint located between the forearm and upper arm.</rdfs:comment>
    <hed:hasHedParent>
      <hed:HedTag rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Upper-extremity">
        <rdfs:label>Upper-extremity</rdfs:label>
        <rdfs:comment>Refers to the whole superior limb (shoulder, arm, elbow, wrist, hand).</rdfs:comment>
        <hed:hasHedParent rdf:resource="https://purl.org/hed/tag#Body-part"/>
      </hed:HedTag>
    </hed:hasHedParent>
  </hed:HedTag>
  <hed:HedUnit rdf:about="https://purl.org/hed/aux#oC">
